Package: paraguaydata
Title: Access and Analyze Open Educational and Labor Data from Paraguay
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Liz Bettina", "Garcia Martinez", , "lizbettinag@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tools to access, download and analyze open data from
    Paraguay's main statistical sources, including the Permanent Household
    Survey (EPHC) from the National Statistics Institute (INE), administrative
    records from the Ministry of Education (MEC), and PISA 2022 results.
    Functions cover educational indicators (enrollment, dropout, years of
    schooling), labor market indicators (unemployment, informality,
    underemployment), multidimensional poverty, SDG 4 monitoring, and
    territorial disaggregation by department. Includes automatic detection of
    newly available INE data and export tools for academic publications in APA
    format. Data is accessed from the INE open data portal
    <https://www.ine.gov.py> and the MEC open data portal
    <https://datos.mec.gov.py>.
